                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18130217-12-victim154 t18130217-12-viclabel72"></join>, Bishopsgate-street. On the 6th of February, about six o'clock in the evening, I was going up <placeName id="t18130217-12-crimeloc73">Barbican</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18130217-12-crimeloc73" type="placeName" value="Barbican"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18130217-12-crimeloc73" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18130217-12-off70 t18130217-12-crimeloc73"></join>. I had got the truck, and three dozen of stout, and a dozen-basket with nine bottles of wine in it. I looked back; I saw the prisoner take out two bottles of wine. I let the truck down, and seized the prisoner. A gentleman assisted me in holding the prisoner. He told me to secure him; the prisoner had put the bottles in his pockets. I told the prisoner he had robbed me. He said, no. I took the bottles of wine out of his pockets, and the officer was sent for. These are the bottles; they are my master's property.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I own that I was wrong. I throw myself on the mercy of the court.</p>
